Guess who got an ASS KICKING, BRAND NEW, DIGITAL FUCKING CAMERA FOR CHRISTMAS?! I did!!! I love it so much. It takes the best pictures, it's twenty times better than that old shitty one we have. Anyway, here are some pictures taken over Christmas Eve and Christmas. If there's a * next to it, that means I took it with the new AWESOME camera. :) Enjoy. I didn't actually take this picture, I was decorating the tree at the time. As you can see, the neighbor's dogs are attacking...I mean playing with my dad, who has a sticker on his head. Oh my god, he's the dumbest dog...I love him. That's Curly, the neighbor's dog we take care of. On his left paw he is sporting a lovley green bandage. He broke his foot, but is too stupid to realize it and insists on moving constantly and playing tennis ball. He is defenetly not the brightest bulb in the crayon box. He also smells like shit. My sister actually took this picture, but that's okay. The ugly one, besides Curly, is me. Like my hat? I didn't exactly dress up that night... Purdy Christmas lights! *A lovley Christmas display by our tree. *Oranges!! *Here's an ordimant on our tree. Awww, that's me when I was four years old! I was so cute...whatever happened? *Another ordimant. My sister was probably about two or three years old. What a cutie. *Another ordimant. My sister in the first grade :) *Tasha, the cuter, smarter, better smelling dog. I <3 Tashie :) She didn't like her gold bow... *My sister and her kick ass guitar! *JULIAN!!! *Julian and Cody! *And finally, yay, the tree! Happy holidays everyone!
